<span class="header1">HEALTH CARE</span>
<p>The occupations in this field help to keep the community healthy by providing health care.</p>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Public Health Care Investigator</span><br /><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/GI/md000590.jpg" width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Public Health Care Investigator" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>If you like to find solutions to problems and solve mysteries, you might become a public health care investigator.  In this job, you would find, prevent, and control diseases.  You would interview patients and gather statistics.  You would report what you found to local and state health departments and physicians.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>You need at least a Bachelor's Degree for this job.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The yearly salary ranges from $15,000 to $36,000.</blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Rehabilitation Counselor</span><br /><br />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>As a rehabilitation counselor, you would help a patient who has had a severe injury or trauma to deal with his/her emotions.  You would also help people who have an illness that leaves them disabled.  You would listen to your clients.  You would give them emotional support. You would also plan support services.  You would refer your clients to other people who could help as well.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>You  need at least a Bachelor's Degree for this job.  Many counselors enter this occupation with a Master's Degree.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The yearly salary ranges from $18,000 to $40,000.</blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Home Health Aide</span><br /><br />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>Demand for home health aides is growing because more sick and elderly people prefer to stay in their homes. As a home health aide, you would help the patient take care of his/her daily activities such as eating and bathing. You would also be in the home to talk and listen to the patient.  This would help to keep the patient's spirits up.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>A high school diploma is needed to be a home health aide.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The yearly salary ranges runs from $10,000 to $16,000.</blockquote>

